locality: 3226 DB. Amatole Mt. Near Hogsback. Laong Hogsback Pass. On the forest margin. 3000 feet. In forest undergrowth.

Kasigau Mt.: a steep granite mountian rising with great cliffs and very steep slopes 1000 m above the surrounding plain, its lower slopes bearing dense thicket and scrub-forest replaced by rainforest with scanty undergrowth but many epiphytes about halfway up, the uppermost slopes with a dense Mimulopsis understory; in lower rainforest.
Longido Forest Reserve, ca. 1.1 km NE of Longido Peak, near lower edge of dry montane forest with Nuxia congesta and Elaeodendron buchananii.
Dabaga Highlands, Kibengu, 18 mi. S of Dabaga.
Natal Cathedral Peak Hotel, along the Cathedral Peak Path. Gallery forest, spreading on the slope of a rivulet, with Podocarpus latifolius, undergrowth of Diospyros whyteana, Carissa bispinosa.
W Usambaras: Mkusu Valley between Mkuzi and Kifungilo.
SW of W Usambara Mts., N ridge of Mafi Hill.
